                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 125.187/2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                    <gloss type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Austria-Hungary</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PFC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-23T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1915, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1052. Your 1017 and 1036.<note n="1" xml:id="d1309fn1">Latter not printed.</note>
                    Inasmuch as there now appear to be practically no American or foreign interests
                    to be cared for in Belgrade, Young should arrange sealing of archives and for
                    safekeeping of Consulate and then proceed to Vienna where he has been
                    temporarily assigned in Consulate General subject to such services as Embassy
                    may require. Detail is, however, only temporary. Belgrade seals should be
                    deposited Vienna Consulate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
